Here is a possible Svelte component for a simple "who am I" landing page:

```html
<div class="landing">
  <h1>Who Am I?</h1>

  <p>Guess the famous person or character I'm thinking of by asking yes or no questions.</p>

  <button on:click={startGame}>Start Game</button>
</div>

<script>
  let gameStarted = false;

  function startGame() {
    gameStarted = true;
    dispatch('startGame');
  }
</script>

<style>
  .landing {
    text-align: center;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  button {
    background: #blue;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    border: none;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }
</style> 
```

This component shows:

- An <h1> "Who Am I?" 
- A <p> with instructions 
- A <button> to start the game
- When the button is clicked, it sets gameStarted = true and dispatches a 'startGame' event
- Some basic styling to center the content and style the elements

You would build on this by:

- Listening for the 'startGame' event in the parent component 
- Showing a new view with the actual guessing game once that event is received
- Keeping track of guesses and providing feedback to the user
- Eventually revealing the answer and showing a final score

Let me know if you have any other questions!

Here's an updated Svelte component that starts the game and provides a guessing interface:

```html
<div class="landing" class:hidden={gameStarted}>
  <!-- landing page content -->
</div>

<div class="game" class:hidden={!gameStarted}>
  <p>I'm thinking of a famous {personOrCharacter}! Ask me yes or no questions to try and guess who it is.</p>

  <div class="questions">
    <input bind:value={question}>
    <button on:click={askQuestion}>Ask</button>
  </div>

  <div class="feedback">
    <p>{feedback}</p>
  </div>

  <button on:click={endGame}>Give Up?</button>
</div>

<script>
  let gameStarted = false;
  let personOrCharacter = 'person'; // or 'character'
  let answer = 'Albert Einstein';
  let question;
  let feedback;

  function startGame() {
    gameStarted = true;
  }

  function askQuestion() {
    if (question.toLowerCase() === 'is it ' + answer.toLowerCase()) {
      feedback = 'You got it! It was ' + answer + '.';
    } else {
      feedback = getFeedback(question);
    }
  }

  function getFeedback(question) {
    // Logic to return 'Yes', 'No' or 'Invalid question' feedback
  }

  function endGame() {
    gameStarted = false;
    feedback = '';
  }
</script>

<style>
 /* styles */ 
</style>
```

This shows:

- The landing page or game interface depending on gameStarted
- Instructions for the user 
- A form to enter a yes/no question 
- Feedback after the user clicks "Ask"
- A "Give Up" button to end the game
- Logic to check the user's guess, provide feedback, and end the game

Let me know if you have any other questions!
